26/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Siljan Avramovski and German experts assisting in the process of police reform held a joint news conference in Skopje on Monday (25 October).
Avramovski said reforms are being implemented, adding that the first priority would be establishment of a special unit for combating organised crime.
In other news, Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva met with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer in Brussels on Monday.
She reiterated Skopje's desire to receive an invitation for membership during the Alliance's next enlargement wave in 2006.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 26/10/04;
Macedonian government Web site - 25/10/04)
